        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 5 at 2:58AM CDT by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 256 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fredericksburg, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Inks Lake State Park, Marble Falls, Sunrise Beach Village, Blowout,
Meadowlakes, Bluffton, Rocky Hill, Baby Head, Stolz, Blumenthal,
Fredericksburg, Kingsland, Crabapple, Grapetown, Oxford, Cherry
Spring, Llano, Lone Grove, Enchanted Rock State Natural Area, and
Cain City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
